
[1]thrice

   THRICE, adv. [from three; perhaps three, and L. vice.]

   1. Three times.

   Before the cock crow, thou shalt deny me thrice. Matt.26.

   2. Sometimes used by way of amplification; very.

   Thrice noble Lord, let me entreat of you

   To pardon me.
